	<pb facs="liv_001196_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
	<!-- Start each page with a <pb> formatted as above -->

<!-- If this is a letter or similar with an opener (with content such as dateline and/or salute) add it. For example: -->
<opener>
<lb/><dateline rend="center"><add rend="left" hand="#U">2</add> <placeName><settlement type="city">Manchester</settlement></placeName> <add rend="right" place="margintop" hand="#U">5</add>
<lb/><!-- There is a postal mark here. SF -->
<lb rend="right"/><date when="1858-01-28">28<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> January<!-- Change line info as appropriate --><!-- Begin each line with <lb/> as here --> 
<lb rend="right"/>1858</date></dateline><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/>    
<lb/><salute>My Dear <persName>Nani</persName></salute><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
</opener>

<lb/><p>I am sorry to
<lb/>hear that your
<lb/>eyes prevent you
<lb/>from reading but
<lb/>every thing that
<lb/>happens to us
<lb/>is by the will

	<pb facs="liv_001196_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>and according to the
<lb/>direction of our
<lb/>supreme Lord in
<lb/>whom we live
<lb/>and move and
<lb/>have our being.
<lb/>Let your heart bow
<lb/>to him in lowly
<lb/>submission. And
<lb/>you may tell him
<lb/>all your concerns
<lb/>fears and cares
<lb/>for truly he

	<pb facs="liv_001196_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>careth for you, high <add rend="right" place="margintop" hand="#U">6</add>
<lb/>and lofty though he be.
<lb/>The Lord bless and
<lb/>keep you.</p>

<lb/><p>We are getting all
<lb/>ready for a start
<lb/>if possible on the 
<lb/><date when="1858-02-15">15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of February</date><supplied cert="high">.</supplied>
<lb/>I came down here
<lb/>to purchase calicoes
<lb/>for presents to the
<lb/><gap extent="1" unit="lines" agent="hole"/> return 
<lb/><gap extent="2" unit="lines" agent="hole"/><!-- I might change this to two different <gap> elements to reflect that you can partially see one line but cannot see anything on the lines after it. EC -->

	<pb facs="liv_001196_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>We went to a meeting
<lb/>of the <orgName>geographical
<lb/>society</orgName> on <date when="1858-01-25"><choice><sic>monday</sic><corr>Monday</corr></choice></date> but
<lb/>failed to reach it
<lb/>through the dense crowd
<lb/>collected to see the
<lb/>illuminations on
<lb/>the occasion of the
<lb/>wedding of the <persName>Princess
<lb/>Royal</persName> - Mama was
<lb/>never so squeezed
<lb/>before. Kind regards
<lb/>to your <term type="occupation">governer</term> and
<lb/>your father's blessing
<lb/><gap extent="3" unit="lines" agent="hole"/></p>

<!-- No closer available because text has been removed. SF -->

